Pour the @water{150%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When 
boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to 
medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the 
pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} 
or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into 
small pieces). Trim the @green beans{80%g} then chop them into thirds.

Chop the @diced chicken breast{260%g} into 2cm chunks. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands 
after handling raw meat. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over 
medium-high heat. Once hot, add the diced chicken pieces and fry until golden, 
turning occasionally until browned on all sides, ~{6-8%minutes}. Season with 
@salt{} and @black pepper{} as it cooks.

Once the chicken has browned, add the shallot and cook until softened, 
~{3-4%minutes} more, stirring occasionally. Once softened, add the 
@korma curry paste{50%g}, @honey{15%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and 
@water{50%ml} for the curry, stir to mix it all together. Add the @crème fraîche{75%g} 
and green beans and stir until fully combined. Bring to the boil and simmer until 
the beans are tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring 
occasionally. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While you wait for everything to finish, have a quick tidy up.

Taste and season the curry with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if you think it needs 
it. Divide the rice between #plates{} and top with the chicken korma curry. 
Enjoy!